Option Grid Changes to show months with value Cc John I went through the code and realized that the change to show months with value is a little big change and cannot be done in hours The problem I see is that when portcalc values a post id it does not create any data in database for the months where you do not have positions What it means it can be done but it will take minimum days to make the changes test it and give it to you Also it will slow down option grid a little more as I need to build rows with values which are not in database I just wanted to give you an update and I will talk to Karima Francis to let them know how we are going to handle it Let me know if you have any questions

RE terminated vs nonterminated requestPST Yes i will be in the office Let me know whenever you need the data dump Regards Sanjeev Original Message From Keiser Kam Sent Tuesday January PM To Gupta Sanjeev Subject FW terminated vs nonterminated request Sanjeev will you be here on Thursday and Friday I will need your help again with a dump of data before the weekend Thanks Original Message From Gossett Jeffrey C Sent Tuesday January PM To Keiser Kam Subject FW terminated vs nonterminated request Enjoy Original Message From Wilson Shona Sent Tuesday January PM To Sweeney Kevin Hall D Todd Hall Bob M Gossett Jeffrey C Albrecht Kristin Miralles Albert Mills Scott Reeves Kathy Gillis Brian Hedstrom Peggy Horn Cindy Thurbin Simon Cc Thapar Raj Beck Sally Pearce Barry Subject terminated vs nonterminated request Now that we have almost all of the Form A information EY needs form B filled out for all commodities We would like to have this as of the deals on Please let me know when you will be able prepare the schedule including a reconciliation to your rolls File EY requestxls Thanks Shona Wilson Director Global Risk Operations X

RE postidsPST It would be my pleasure Let me know whenever you have the post id I will try to finish it up tonight itself Thanks Sanjeev x Original Message From Keiser Kam Sent Thursday January PM To Gupta Sanjeev Subject postids Sanjeev I should have a list of postids for you by today After friday I will no longer have access to the estate so if you could shoot this off over night so I could have something in the morning to work with I would appreciate it Let me know if that doesnt seem possible Thanks Kam

Changes in TAGG Deal Capture Screen Cc PST We have a new version of TAGG Deal Capture Application under TAGGStage Following enhancements made in this version A new flag has been added in the deal capture screen that will allow a particular deal record to be identified as a component of a multilegged deal Requested by TAGG Deal Clearing Ron Nolte x Reason TAGG Deal Clearing has a process that sends confirmation related information to Commodity Logic However there are some TAGG deals that are made up of different legs In these cases Commodity Logic does not want to get any of the legs associated with multileg deals Please note that creating more than one leg for a deal does not mean that it is a multi legged deal Allow entry of negative price values in fixed price column of Deal Capture Application for SwapsForwardOptions only Requested by Victor Guggenheim Reason Negative Price Curve for Freight has been loaded into the system without any problem but user interfaceTAGG Deal Capture does not accept negative values The new version is planned to be migrated to production for July or If you encounter any problems please let me know Thunderball EOL bridge and TAGG Server and TDS system support personnel please verify if you are okay with change If you have any questions you can contact me x or Oscar X Regards Sanjeev X
